*****
[2
Date: 1 Mar 2001
From: Bapen <bapen@earthlink.net>
Source: Associated Press, 1 Mar 2001 [edited

Britain and Ireland struggled Thursday to contain an outbreak of FMD, and
the first cases in Scotland were confirmed at farms near Lockerbie.
Scotland confirmed its first cases on a farm in Lockerbie and another in
nearby Canonbie. Cattle from the farms will be slaughtered, the Scottish
Executive said. The cases were linked to shipments from Britain before it
halted livestock movement, chief veterinary officer Jim Scudamore said.
